tive as a fusion of Mark Twain and Gertrude Stein. Taken together, these pieces provide a rich oral history of and critical context for the evolution of the California art scene from the 1960s onward.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aArtszCalifornia. 0aPerformance artvTexts. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  a1960s.  a20th century.  aanalysis.  aart and literature.  acomedy.  aconcept of time.  acontemporary poetry.  aexperience of time.  afamous poets.  afreeform poetry.  aimprovised poetry.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary critics.  alived experiences.  amemory.  amodern poets.  amuseums.  anew york.  aoral history.  aperformance art.  apoetry centers.  apoetry collection.  apoets.  asouthern california.  atalk poems.  atemporal states.  athinking out loud.  atime.  auniversities.  averbal invention.  averbal poems.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024305740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093829840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938298423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938298/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY